    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've written:\n\n## PulseBoard Channel Plugin — Plan Overview\n\n**16 new files**, all under `extensions/pulseboard/`. No existing files are touched.\n\n### PulseBoard-specific design decisions\n- **Boards** use a `!boardname` prefix (distinguishes groups from DMs; e.g. `!general`)\n- **DMs** use bare usernames (e.g. `alice`)\n- **Config keys**: `serverUrl`, `apiToken`, `username`, `boards[]` — with env var fallbacks `PULSEBOARD_SERVER_URL`, `PULSEBOARD_USERNAME`, `PULSEBOARD_API_TOKEN`\n- **Chat types**: `[\"direct\", \"group\"]`\n- **Text chunk limit**: `4000` characters (set in `outbound.base.textChunkLimit`)\n- Protocol implementation is stubbed (fictional platform), but the full architectural skeleton is real and wired\n\n### Files at a glance\n\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `package.json` | `@openclaw/pulseboard`, channel metadata |\n| `openclaw.plugin.json` | `id: \"pulseboard\"`, naming invariants satisfied |\n| `index.ts` | `defineChannelPluginEntry` |\n| `setup-entry.ts` | `defineSetupPluginEntry` |\n| `api.ts` | Public barrel: re-exports accounts + setup surface |\n| `src/types.ts` | `PulseboardAccountConfig`, `CoreConfig`, `PulseboardProbe`, etc. |\n| `src/config-schema.ts` | Zod schema + `buildChannelConfigSchema` |\n| `src/accounts.ts` | `resolvePulseboardAccount`, list/default helpers |\n| `src/normalize.ts` | Target normalization (`!board`, bare user, prefix stripping) |\n| `src/runtime.ts` | `createPluginRuntimeStore` store |\n| `src/runtime-api.ts` | SDK barrel (no dedicated `plugin-sdk/pulseboard` facade needed) |\n| `src/send.ts` | `sendMessagePulseboard` (stubbed HTTP call) |\n| `src/probe.ts` | `probePulseboard` (stubbed health check) |\n| `src/setup-core.ts` | `pulseboardSetupAdapter` + config patch helpers |\n| `src/setup-surface.ts` | `pulseboardSetupWizard` (full wizard flow) |\n| `src/channel.ts` | `createChatChannelPlugin` with all adapters wired |\n\n### Verification\n- `pnpm test -- src/plugins/bundled-plugin-naming.test.ts` — naming invariants\n- `pnpm tsgo` — type check\n- `pnpm check` — lint/format",
